Jersey_City.County Prep High School:
County Prep High School is a full-time public magnet high school for students in ninth through twelfth grades, located in Jersey City in Hudson County, New Jersey, United States, operating as part of the Hudson County Schools of Technology.
As of the 2014-15 school year, the school had an enrollment of 708 students and 81.8 classroom teachers (on an FTE basis), for a student–teacher ratio of 8.7:1. There were 297 students (41.9% of enrollment) eligible for free lunch and 105 (14.8% of students) eligible for reduced-cost lunch.
